{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3571","heading":"Sentence of fine","label":"3571 Sentence of fine","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/ptII/ch227/schC","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Prior ProvisionsFor a prior section 3571, applicable to offenses committed prior to , see note set out preceding .Nov. 1, 1987section 3551 of this title","Amendments1987— amended section generally, revising and restating as subsecs. (a) to (e) provisions formerly contained in subsecs. (a) and (b).Pub. L. 100–185","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective , and applicable only to offenses committed after the taking effect of this section, see , set out as a note under .Nov. 1, 1987section 235(a)(1) of Pub. L. 98–473section 3551 of this title"],"amendments":["Amendments1987— amended section generally, revising and restating as subsecs. (a) to (e) provisions formerly contained in subsecs. (a) and (b).Pub. L. 100–185"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—In General","label":"a .—In General","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A defendant who has been found guilty of an offense may be sentenced to pay a fine.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Fines for Individuals","label":"b .—Fines for Individuals","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the amount specified in the law setting forth the offense;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the applicable amount under subsection (d) of this section;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for a felony, not more than $250,000;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for a misdemeanor resulting in death, not more than $250,000;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for a Class A misdemeanor that does not result in death, not more than $100,000;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fb%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for a Class B or C misdemeanor that does not result in death, not more than $5,000; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fb%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for an infraction, not more than $5,000.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Fines for Organizations","label":"c .—Fines for Organizations","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the amount specified in the law setting forth the offense;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the applicable amount under subsection (d) of this section;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for a felony, not more than $500,000;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for a misdemeanor resulting in death, not more than $500,000;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fc%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for a Class A misdemeanor that does not result in death, not more than $200,000;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fc%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for a Class B or C misdemeanor that does not result in death, not more than $10,000; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fc%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for an infraction, not more than $10,000.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Alternative Fine Based on Gain or Loss","label":"d .—Alternative Fine Based on Gain or Loss","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"If any person derives pecuniary gain from the offense, or if the offense results in pecuniary loss to a person other than the defendant, the defendant may be fined not more than the greater of twice the gross gain or twice the gross loss, unless imposition of a fine under this subsection would unduly complicate or prolong the sentencing process.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Special Rule for Lower Fine Specified in Substantive Provision","label":"e .—Special Rule for Lower Fine Specified in Substantive Provision","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s3571","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs3571%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"If a law setting forth an offense specifies no fine or a fine that is lower than the fine otherwise applicable under this section and such law, by specific reference, exempts the offense from the applicability of the fine otherwise applicable under this section, the defendant may not be fined more than the amount specified in the law setting forth the offense.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
